u might treat this as <samp>UI</samp> or as <samp>FAIL</samp>.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:api-help-authmanagerhelper-additional-params',_binary 's:344:\"en:This module accepts additional parameters depending on the available authentication requests. Use <kbd>[[Special:ApiHelp/query+authmanagerinfo|action=query&meta=authmanagerinfo]]</kbd> with <kbd>amirequestsfor=$1</kbd> (or a previous response from this module, if applicable) to determine the requests available and the fields that they use.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:api-help-authmanagerhelper-continue',_binary 's:152:\"en:This request is a continuation after an earlier <samp>UI</samp> or <samp>REDIRECT</samp> response. Either this or <var>$1returnurl</var> is required.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:api-help-authmanagerhelper-mergerequestfields',_binary 's:74:\"en:Merge field information for all authentication requests into one array.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:api-help-authmanagerhelper-messageformat',_binary 's:40:\"en:Format to use for returning messages.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:api-help-authmanagerhelper-preservestate',_binary 's:68:\"en:Preserve state from a previous failed login attempt, if possible.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:api-help-authmanagerhelper-request',_binary 's:194:\"en:Use this authentication request, by the <samp>id</samp> returned from <kbd>[[Special:ApiHelp/query+authmanagerinfo|action=query&meta=authmanagerinfo]]</kbd> with <kbd>amirequestsfor=$1</kbd>.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:api-help-authmanagerhelper-requests',_binary 's:246:\"en:Only use these authentication requests, by the <samp>id</samp> returned from <kbd>[[Special:ApiHelp/query+authmanagerinfo|action=query&meta=authmanagerinfo]]</kbd> with <kbd>amirequestsfor=$1</kbd> or from a previous response from this module.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:api-help-authmanagerhelper-returnurl',_binary 's:517:\"en:Return URL for third-party authentication flows, must b