ry 's:129:\"en:If specified, encodes all non-ASCII using hexadecimal escape sequences. Default when <var>formatversion</var> is <kbd>1</kbd>.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-json-param-callback',_binary 's:116:\"en:If specified, wraps the output into a given function call. For safety, all user-specific data will be restricted.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-json-param-formatversion',_binary 's:20:\"en:Output formatting\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-json-param-utf8',_binary 's:193:\"en:If specified, encodes most (but not all) non-ASCII characters as UTF-8 instead of replacing them with hexadecimal escape sequences. Default when <var>formatversion</var> is not <kbd>1</kbd>.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-json-paramvalue-formatversion-1',_binary 's:97:\"en:Backwards-compatible format (XML-style booleans, <samp>*</samp> keys for content nodes, etc.).\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-json-paramvalue-formatversion-2',_binary 's:17:\"en:Modern format.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-json-paramvalue-formatversion-latest',_binary 's:78:\"en:Use the latest format (currently <kbd>2</kbd>), may change without warning.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-json-summary',_binary 's:30:\"en:Output data in JSON format.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-jsonfm-summary',_binary 's:53:\"en:Output data in JSON format (pretty-print in HTML).\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-link',_binary 's:28:\"en:[[Special:ApiHelp/$1|$2]]\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-linkaccount-example-link',_binary 's:70:\"en:Start the process of linking to an account from <kbd>Example</kbd>.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-linkaccount-summary',_binary 's:67:\"en:Link an account from a third-party provider to the current user.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-login-example-login',_binary 's:10:\"en:Log in.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-login-extended-description',_binary 's:256:\"en:This action should only be used in combination with [[Special:BotPasswords]]; use for main-account login is deprecated and may fail without warning. To safely log in to the main account, use <kbd>[[Special:ApiHelp/clientlogin|action=clientlogin]]</kbd>.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-login-extended-description-nobotpasswords',_binary 's:143:\"en:This action is deprecated and may fail without warning. To safely log in, use <kbd>[[Special:ApiHelp/clientlogin|action=clientlogin]]</kbd>.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-login-param-domain',_binary 's:21:\"en:Domain (optional).\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-login-param-name',_binary 's:12:\"en:Username.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-login-param-password',_binary 's:12:\"en:Password.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-login-param-token',_binary 's:41:\"en:Login token obtained in first request.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-login-summary',_binary 's:41:\"en:Log in and get authentication cookies.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-logout-example-logout',_binary 's:28:\"en:Log the current user out.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-logout-summary',_binary 's:34:\"en:Log out and clear session data.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-main-extended-description',_binary 's:1342:\"en:<div class=\"hlist plainlinks api-main-links\">\n* [[mw:Special:MyLanguage/API:Main_page|Documentation]]\n* [[mw:Special:MyLanguage/API:Etiquette|Etiquette & usage guidelines]]\n* [[mw:Special:MyLanguage/API:FAQ|FAQ]]\n* [https://lists.wikimedia.org/postorius/lists/mediawiki-api.lists.wikimedia.org/ Mailing list]\n* [https://lists.wikimedia.org/postorius/lists/mediawiki-api-announce.lists.wikimedia.org/ API Announcements]\n* [https://phabricator.wikimedia.org/maniphest/query/GebfyV4uCaLd/#R Bugs & requests]\n</div>\n<strong>Status:</strong> The MediaWiki API is a mature and stable interface that is actively supported and improved. While we try to avoid it, we may occasionally need to make breaking changes; subscribe to [https://lists.wikimedia.org/hyperkitty/list/mediawiki-api-announce@lists.wikimedia.org/ the mediawiki-api-announce mailing list] for notice of updates.\n\n<strong>Erroneous requests:</strong> When erroneous requests are sent to the API, an HTTP header will be sent with the key \"MediaWiki-API-Error\" and then both the value of the header and the error code sent back will be set to the same value. For more information see [[mw:Special:MyLanguage/API:Errors_and_warnings|API: Errors and warnings]].\n\n<p class=\"mw-apisandbox-link\"><strong>Testing:</strong> For ease of testing API requests, see [[Special:ApiSandbox]].</p>\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-main-param-action',_binary 's:27:\"en:Which action to perform.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-main-param-assert',_binary 's:199:\"en:Verify that the user is logged in (including possibly as a temporary user) if set to <kbd>user</kbd>, <em>not</em> logged in if set to <kbd>anon</kbd>, or has the bot user right if <kbd>bot</kbd>.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-main-param-assertuser',_binary 's:45:\"en:Verify the current user is the named user.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-main-param-curtimestamp',_binary 's:47:\"en:Include the current timestamp in the result.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-main-param-errorformat',_binary 's:50:\"en:Format to use for warning and error text output\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-main-param-errorlang',_binary 's:311:\"en:Language to use for warnings and errors. <kbd>[[Special:ApiHelp/query+siteinfo|action=query&meta=siteinfo&siprop=languages]]</kbd> returns a list of language codes. Specify <kbd>content</kbd> to use this wiki\'s content language or <kbd>uselang</kbd> to use the same value as the <var>uselang</var> parameter.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-main-param-errorsuselocal',_binary 's:98:\"en:If given, error texts will use locally-customized messages from the {{ns:MediaWiki}} namespace.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-main-param-format',_binary 's:28:\"en:The format of the output.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-main-param-maxage',_binary 's:104:\"en:Set the <code>max-age</code> HTTP cache control header to this many seconds. Errors are never cached.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-main-param-maxlag',_binary 's:491:\"en:Maximum lag can be used when MediaWiki is installed on a database replicated cluster. To save actions causing any more site replication lag, this parameter can make the client wait until the replication lag is less than the specified value. In case of excessive lag, error code <samp>maxlag</samp> is returned with a message like <samp>Waiting for $host: $lag seconds lagged</samp>.<br />See [[mw:Special:MyLanguage/Manual:Maxlag_parameter|Manual: Maxlag parameter]] for more information.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-main-param-origin',_binary 's:1008:\"en:When accessing the API using a cross-domain AJAX request (CORS), set this to the originating domain. This must be included in any pre-flight request, and therefore must be part of the request URI (not the POST body).\n\nFor authenticated requests, this must match one of the origins in the <code>Origin</code> header exactly, so it has to be set to something like <kbd>https://en.wikipedia.org</kbd> or <kbd>https://meta.wikimedia.org</kbd>. If this parameter does not match the <code>Origin</code> header, a 403 response will be returned. If this parameter matches the <code>Origin</code> header and the origin is allowed, the <code>Access-Control-Allow-Origin</code> and <code>Access-Control-Allow-Credentials</code> headers will be set.\n\nFor non-authenticated requests, specify the value <kbd>*</kbd>. This will cause the <code>Access-Control-Allow-Origin</code> header to be set, but <code>Access-Control-Allow-Credentials</code> will be <code>false</code> and all user-specific data will be restricted.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-main-param-requestid',_binary 's:94:\"en:Any value given here will be included in the response. May be used to distinguish requests.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-main-param-responselanginfo',_binary 's:92:\"en:Include the languages used for <var>uselang</var> and <var>errorlang</var> in the result.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-main-param-servedby',_binary 's:63:\"en:Include the hostname that served the request in the results.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-main-param-smaxage',_binary 's:105:\"en:Set the <code>s-maxage</code> HTTP cache control header to this many seconds. Errors are never cached.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-main-param-uselang',_binary 's:305:\"en:Language to use for message translations. <kbd>[[Special:ApiHelp/query+siteinfo|action=query&meta=siteinfo&siprop=languages]]</kbd> returns a list of language codes. You can specify <kbd>user</kbd> to use the current user\'s language preference or <kbd>content</kbd> to use this wiki\'s content language.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-main-param-variant',_binary 's:88:\"en:Variant of the language. Only works if the base language supports variant conversion.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-main-paramvalue-errorformat-bc',_binary 's:103:\"en:Format used prior to MediaWiki 1.29. <var>errorlang</var> and <var>errorsuselocal</var> are ignored.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-main-paramvalue-errorformat-html',_binary 's:7:\"en:HTML\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-main-paramvalue-errorformat-none',_binary 's:40:\"en:No text output, only the error codes.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-main-paramvalue-errorformat-plaintext',_binary 's:57:\"en:Wikitext with HTML tags removed and entities replaced.\";'),(_binary 'en',_binary 'messages:apihelp-main-paramvalue-errorformat-